- Supabase only, no fallback

I need to restore a fallback. If Supabase isn't configured or fails, it should fall through to mock data so the app is always usable. This was one of the key design decisions in BLUEPRINT.md: "Three-tier fallback: local Express → Supabase → in-memory mock data, so app always usable."

Let me rewrite the auth-store to have proper fallback. The key logic:
1. If `NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL` is set (not placeholder), try Supabase first
2. If that fails or isn't configured, fall back to mock data
3. Mock login: accept any email/password, determine role from email prefix or default

